parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Seat Belt Buckle Release Mechanism
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle release mechanism can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to inadequate restraint in the event of an accident, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle is difficult to latch or unlatch
the seat belt buckle fails to latch
the seat belt buckle is stuck
the seat belt fails to restrain the driver or passenger during an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Repair of Recalled Seat Belt Buckles
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to properly repair recalled seat belt buckles can lead to continued malfunction of the seat belt system, putting drivers and passengers at risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The dealer fails to have the necessary parts for the repair
the repair is delayed or incomplete
the seat belt buckle fails to function properly after repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Seat Belt Failure to Restrain During Accidents
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt to restrain the driver or passenger during an accident can result in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The seat belt fails to restrain the driver or passenger during an accident
the driver or passenger is ejected from the vehicle
the seat belt fails to deploy properly.
